---
title: Double Mediterranean Salmon & Winter Veggie Toss with Garlic Spinach & Balsamic Glaze
description: Salmon is always nice cooked with light flavours, but a dark and rich balsamic glaze with delicious root veggies in a cosy winter toss might be the new best way to eat salmon.

*Unfortunately, this
week's silverbeet was in
short supply, so we've
replaced it with baby
spinach. Don't worry,
the recipe will be just as
delicious, just be sure to
follow your recipe card!*
